Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel) and pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @slow cooked beef{280%grams} from the packaging. Place in an #ovenproof dish{} along with the juices. Sprinkle the @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} over the beef, then turn the beef over a few times so it's well coated. Cover loosely with #foil{}.

> Add less Cajun spice mix if you'd prefer things milder.

Roast on the middle shelf for ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the beef is piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, pop the @garlic cloves{2} (unpeeled) into a small piece of foil with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel in the oven until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}. Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

Halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2} as thinly as you can. Pop it into a small #bowl{}.

Squeeze in some lime juice, add the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and a pinch of salt, mix together and set aside to pickle.

Cut the @medium tomatoes{2} into 1cm chunks and pop into another small bowl. Drizzle over some oil, squeeze in some lime juice, season with salt and pepper and mix together. Set your salsa aside.

In another small bowl, combine the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and lime zest. Season with salt and pepper and mix together. Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin, mash with a #fork{} and stir into the mayo. Loosen with a splash of water if needed so that it drizzles nicely.

Once the beef is cooked, remove it from the oven, reserve 1 tbsp of cooking juices per person, then discard the foil and any remaining cooking juices.

Use two #forks{} to shred the beef as finely as you can, season with salt and pepper, then stir in the @BBQ sauce{48%grams} and reserved cooking juices.

Share the wedges between your serving #bowls{} and spoon over the BBQ Cajun beef. Top with the salsa, cheese and pickled onion. Drizzle over the roasted garlic mayo to finish. Enjoy!